Package: R.rsp
Version: 0.9.0
Depends: R (>= 2.5.0), R.utils (>= 1.19.5), R.devices (>= 2.1.3)
Imports: R.methodsS3 (>= 1.4.2), R.oo (>= 1.11.7), R.utils (>= 1.19.5)
Suggests: tcltk, knitr
Date: 2013-02-13
Title: Dynamic generation of scientific reports
Author: Henrik Bengtsson <henrikb@braju.com>
Maintainer: Henrik Bengtsson <henrikb@braju.com>
Description: An RSP document is a text-based document containing an R-embedded template of the final document, e.g. "Today's date is <%=Sys.Date()%>".  An RSP document is preprocessed, parsed and translated into an R script, which when sourced generates the final document.  This way it is possible to dynamically generate reports in plain text, HTML, TeX etc, e.g. "\includegraphics{<%=toPDF('Normal', { curve(dnorm, from=-5, to=+5) })%>}". It can also be used to enhance other literate programming languages such as Sweave and knitr, e.g. "<<eval=<%=doEval%>>>= [...] @".  As explained in one of the vignettes, RSP-embedded LaTeX vignettes can easily be included in any R package.
License: LGPL (>= 2.1)
LazyLoad: TRUE
